-- Ukrainian President Wants Currency Corridor, Interfax Reports
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-07-03T13:14:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-03/ukrainian-president-wants-currency-corridor-interfax-reports.html
Ukrainian President  Viktor Yanukovych 
said the national currency, the hryvnia, needs a trading band,
Interfax-Ukraine newswire reported, citing an address by
Yanukovych to parliament, the text of which was handed out to
lawmakers.  The Kiev-based  Natsionalnyi Bank Ukrainy  controls the
hryvnia exchange rate by buying or selling dollars on the
interbank market.  -- Editors: Elizabeth Konstantinova, Andrew Langley  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
